'''Transparency Options''' allows the appearance of buildings and other types of objects to be toggled. The ''Transparency Options'' toolbar can be accessed either by selecting ''Transparancy Options'' from the options menu ([[File:en/Manual/Options button.png]]), or using <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">ctrl</span> + <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">X</span>. All [[en/Manual/Transparency options#locked-transparency-options|unlocked transparency options]] can be quicky toggled on/off by pressing <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">X</span>. 
For each type of object setting the corresponding button in the toolbar or using <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">ctrl</span> + (<span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">1</span> to <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">9</span>) will allow the player to see behind it. The current appearance of a type of object can be ''locked'' against being toggled with <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">X</span> by applying <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">ctrl</span> + <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">click</span> on its option button. Objects can be set to invisible instead of transparent by clicking on the appropriate button in the second row, or by the hotkeys <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">shift</span> + <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">ctrl</span> + (<span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">1</span> to <span style="font: small-caps 0.85em sans-serif; padding: 1px 3px; background-color: whitesmoke; border: solid darkgray; border-width: 1px 1px 2px; border-radius: 3px;">9</span>).

===Transparency Options Toolbar===
[[File:en/Manual/TransparencyOptions.png]]<br>
The Transparency Options toolbar has two rows:
*The first row defines what map feature is affected, and if it is locked.
*The second row defines what map feature should be invisible ''or'' transparent when the first row is set.

